{
  "stem": "26142.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was the first time-- you know, I was about 15-years-old-- I-- I really started to realize what was going on, that the-- they were talking in the house, that his family was living in-- in-- in Frankfurt, in the city.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had to leave or how exactly, I don't-- I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But that they were refugees, they lost.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's how it first started to affect me-- as-- as to realize that something is wrong.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and-- we-- we didn't-- in Czechoslovakia, in-- at that time, we didn't-- we didn't feel anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And for the simple reason because the Czech government knew that there is 10% of the population that was in Carpathia was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You have to remember that the Carpathian area was included in Czechoslovakia under the agreement of the-- of the first [?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Felkerbund ?] that was organized.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Like the United Nations was organized after World War II, the [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Felkerbund ?] was organized after World War I.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's when the-- the-- the Austrian-Hungarian empire was-- fell apart and-- and the Czechoslovakia was-- was-- came to existence as an independent state.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the Ruthenia, that Carpathian area, was given to them under a autonomy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had full-- they had full autonomy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they-- they had to have-- they knew that maybe they have different aspirations.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So the-- they knew that the Jewish people had no-- no aspirations for-- for themselves in that autonomy, except to live under a democratic country.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So-- and they-- so we-- we enjoyed, more or less, a-- a-- they knew that we were loyal citizens.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they needed us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the Zionist movement was to, first of all, to-- to learn Hebrew, number one.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And number two, it was the movement to-- to return to Zion.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
